        <div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
          <h2 id="transform-your-legacy-applications-to-run-in-cloud">
            Transform your legacy applications&nbsp;to run in&nbsp;Cloud&nbsp;
          </h2>

          <p>
            Very often organizations feel pressure to move to the Cloud without
            fully understanding the level of their readiness to operate in a new
            infrastructure paradigm. It’s true that during migration from the
            traditional data-center approach to the Cloud, applications need to
            be tuned up for the new environment and requirements like security
            and scaling should be taken into account. Such changes need a
            specific competency which is not often present within traditional
            development teams. Sometimes it’s due to limited experience with
            Cloud architectures and frameworks, or lacking the best practices in
            combining Cloud-native features with traditional container-based on
            VM-based applications. But a reliable Cloud software development
            partner can fill this gap.
          </p>

          <p>
            Cloud offers numerous possibilities in terms of agility,
            scalability, and performance. But to fully leverage its immense
            potential and keeping the cost efficiency, oftentimes application
            modernization services are required first.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

      <p>
        Modernizing your on-premise, legacy applications means investing in your
        company’s strong foundation. Cyber Craft modernization experts work with
        clients on launching their Cloud migration initiatives. Our migration
        solutions help enterprises to seamlessly host their existing
        applications on the Cloud, making it more flexible and auto-scaled as
        per demand. This also helps existing teams to get up to speed with
        technology faster and avoid costly mistakes.
      </p>

        <div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
          <h2>Why Cloud modernization</h2>

          <p>
            To manage cost efficiency within continuously changing market
            environments, businesses need to maintain their agility. It enables
            you to link your costs to actual service usage, on one hand, and
            gives an ability to deliver features and fixes extremely fast on
            another. That’s why application modernization is only one step on
            your Cloud journey, but a very important one. To be better aligned
            with the new Cloud environment, you need to customize your
            applications. Here’s why you need to refactor your application with
            the following assumptions:
          </p>

          <div class="wp-bootstrap-blocks-row row">
            <div class="col-12 col-md-6 border-separated-col">
              <ul id="block-cc4b7f3f-b558-4849-b31d-2f6ffbf249c5">
                <li>
                  <strong>Avoid Monolithic, tightly coupled application</strong>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Dependency on physical resources</strong></li>
                <li>
                  <strong
                    >Avoid stateful programming, stateless is the key for fast
                    scaling</strong
                  >
                </li>
                <li><strong>Increase scalability and performance</strong></li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12 col-md-6 border-separated-col">
              <ul id="block-9b65ab6a-4039-4324-a74f-a6834ddd39ad">
                <li>
                  <strong
                    >Eliminate high cost of licensing, e.g. move from Oracle to
                    AWS RDS Postgres</strong
                  >
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong
                    >Enhance end-user experience, it could be a good time to
                    refresh your UI/UX</strong
                  >
                </li>
                <li>
                  <strong
                    >Adoption to DevOps best practices with using CI/CD for
                    smooth release and upgrade</strong
                  >
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
